The paper deals with a matching problem with budget constraints and truthfulness conditions, which are typical topics in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design. The problem is formulated on a bipartite graph, which is a fundamental data structure in computer science (cs.DS). The proposed algorithm is based on a randomized secretary model, which is a common technique in online algorithms and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses applications in wireless networks, which fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
